verses.text_plain: And Adam knew Eve his wife; and she conceived, and bare Cain, and said, I have gotten a man from the Lord.
verses.verse_html:
1And Adam knew Eve his wife; and she conceived, and bare Cain, and said, I have gotten a man from the Lord. ▼
▼ Cain: that is, Gotten, or, Acquired

footnotes.body_text: ▼ Cain: that is, Gotten, or, Acquired
footnotes.body_html: ▼ Cain: that is, Gotten, or, Acquired

verses.text_plain: And she again bare his brother Abel. And Abel was a keeper of sheep, but Cain was a tiller of the ground.
verses.verse_html:
2And she again bare his brother Abel. And Abel was a keeper of sheep, but Cain was a tiller of the ground. ▼
▼ Abel: Heb. Hebel
 , ▼
▼ a keeper: Heb. a feeder

footnotes.body_html: ▼ a keeper: Heb. a feeder

verses.text_plain: And in process of time it came to pass, that Cain brought of the fruit of the ground an offering unto the Lord.
verses.verse_html:
3And in process of time it came to pass, that Cain brought of the fruit of the ground an offering unto the Lord. ▼
▼ in process…: Heb. at the end of days

tokens.text: it came to pass, that Cain

footnotes.body_text: ▼ in process…: Heb. at the end of days
footnotes.body_html: ▼ in process…: Heb. at the end of days

verses.text_plain: And Abel, he also brought of the firstlings of his flock and of the fat thereof. And the Lord had respect unto Abel and to his offering:
verses.verse_html:
4And Abel, he also brought of the firstlings of his flock and of the fat thereof. And the Lord had respect unto Abel and to his offering: ▼
▼ flock: Heb. sheep, or, goats

footnotes.body_html: ▼ flock: Heb. sheep, or, goats

verses.text_plain: But unto Cain and to his offering he had not respect. And Cain was very wroth, and his countenance fell.
verses.verse_html: 5But unto Cain and to his offering he had not respect. And Cain was very wroth, and his countenance fell.

verses.text_plain: And the Lord said unto Cain, Why art thou wroth? and why is thy countenance fallen?
verses.verse_html: 6And the Lord said unto Cain, Why art thou wroth? and why is thy countenance fallen?

verses.text_plain: If thou doest well, shalt thou not be accepted? and if thou doest not well, sin lieth at the door. And unto thee shall be his desire, and thou shalt rule over him.
verses.verse_html:
7If thou doest well, shalt thou not be accepted? and if thou doest not well, sin lieth at the door. And unto thee shall be his desire, and thou shalt rule over him. ▼
▼ be accepted: or, have the excellency
 , ▼
▼ unto…: or, subject unto thee

tokens.text: and if thou doest not well

footnotes.body_text: ▼ be accepted: or, have the excellency
footnotes.body_html: ▼ be accepted: or, have the excellency
▼ unto…: or, subject unto thee

verses.text_plain: And Cain talked with Abel his brother: and it came to pass, when they were in the field, that Cain rose up against Abel his brother, and slew him.
verses.verse_html: 8And Cain talked with Abel his brother: and it came to pass, when they were in the field, that Cain rose up against Abel his brother, and slew him.

tokens.text: and it came to pass, when they were in the field

verses.text_plain: And the Lord said unto Cain, Where is Abel thy brother? And he said, I know not: Am I my brother’s keeper?
verses.verse_html: 9And the Lord said unto Cain, Where is Abel thy brother? And he said, I know not: Am I my brother’s keeper?

verses.text_plain: And he said, What hast thou done? the voice of thy brother’s blood crieth unto me from the ground.
verses.verse_html:
10And he said, What hast thou done? the voice of thy brother’s blood crieth unto me from the ground. ▼
▼ blood: Heb. bloods

verses.text_plain: And now art thou cursed from the earth, which hath opened her mouth to receive thy brother’s blood from thy hand;
verses.verse_html: 11And now art thou cursed from the earth, which hath opened her mouth to receive thy brother’s blood from thy hand;

verses.text_plain: When thou tillest the ground, it shall not henceforth yield unto thee her strength; a fugitive and a vagabond shalt thou be in the earth.
verses.verse_html: 12When thou tillest the ground, it shall not henceforth yield unto thee her strength; a fugitive and a vagabond shalt thou be in the earth.

tokens.text: shalt thou be in the earth

verses.text_plain: And Cain said unto the Lord, My punishment is greater than I can bear.
verses.verse_html:
13And Cain said unto the Lord, My punishment is greater than I can bear. ▼
▼ My…: or, Mine iniquity is greater than that it may be forgiven

footnotes.body_text: ▼ My…: or, Mine iniquity is greater than that it may be forgiven
footnotes.body_html: ▼ My…: or, Mine iniquity is greater than that it may be forgiven

verses.text_plain: Behold, thou hast driven me out this day from the face of the earth; and from thy face shall I be hid; and I shall be a fugitive and a vagabond in the earth; and it shall come to pass, that every one that findeth me shall slay me.
verses.verse_html: 14Behold, thou hast driven me out this day from the face of the earth; and from thy face shall I be hid; and I shall be a fugitive and a vagabond in the earth; and it shall come to pass, that every one that findeth me shall slay me.

tokens.text: Behold, thou hast driven me out
and I shall be a fugitive
and it shall come to pass

verses.text_plain: And the Lord said unto him, Therefore whosoever slayeth Cain, vengeance shall be taken on him sevenfold. And the Lord set a mark upon Cain, lest any finding him should kill him.
verses.verse_html: 15And the Lord said unto him, Therefore whosoever slayeth Cain, vengeance shall be taken on him sevenfold. And the Lord set a mark upon Cain, lest any finding him should kill him.

verses.text_plain: And Cain went out from the presence of the Lord, and dwelt in the land of Nod, on the east of Eden.
verses.verse_html: 16And Cain went out from the presence of the Lord, and dwelt in the land of Nod, on the east of Eden.

verses.text_plain: And Cain knew his wife; and she conceived, and bare Enoch: and he builded a city, and called the name of the city, after the name of his son, Enoch.
verses.verse_html:
17And Cain knew his wife; and she conceived, and bare Enoch: and he builded a city, and called the name of the city, after the name of his son, Enoch. ▼
▼ Enoch: Heb. Chanoch

verses.text_plain: And unto Enoch was born Irad: and Irad begat Mehujael: and Mehujael begat Methusael: and Methusael begat Lamech.
verses.verse_html:
18And unto Enoch was born Irad: and Irad begat Mehujael: and Mehujael begat Methusael: and Methusael begat Lamech. ▼
▼ Lamech: Heb. Lemech

verses.text_plain: And Lamech took unto him two wives: the name of the one was Adah, and the name of the other Zillah.
verses.verse_html: 19And Lamech took unto him two wives: the name of the one was Adah, and the name of the other Zillah.

verses.text_plain: And Adah bare Jabal: he was the father of such as dwell in tents, and of such as have cattle.
verses.verse_html: 20And Adah bare Jabal: he was the father of such as dwell in tents, and of such as have cattle.

verses.text_plain: And his brother’s name was Jubal: he was the father of all such as handle the harp and organ.
verses.verse_html: 21And his brother’s name was Jubal: he was the father of all such as handle the harp and organ.

verses.text_plain: And Zillah, she also bare Tubal–cain, an instructer of every artificer in brass and iron: and the sister of Tubal–cain was Naamah.
verses.verse_html:
22And Zillah, she also bare Tubal–cain, an instructer of every artificer in brass and iron: and the sister of Tubal–cain was Naamah. ▼
▼ instructer: Heb. whetter

verses.text_plain: And Lamech said unto his wives, Adah and Zillah, Hear my voice; ye wives of Lamech, hearken unto my speech: for I have slain a man to my wounding, and a young man to my hurt.
verses.verse_html:
23And Lamech said unto his wives, Adah and Zillah, Hear my voice; ye wives of Lamech, hearken unto my speech: for I have slain a man to my wounding, and a young man to my hurt. ▼
▼ I have…: or, I would slay a man in my wound, etc.
 , ▼
▼ to my hurt: or, in my hurt

footnotes.body_text: ▼ I have…: or, I would slay a man in my wound, etc.
footnotes.body_html: ▼ I have…: or, I would slay a man in my wound, etc.

footnotes.body_text: ▼ to my hurt: or, in my hurt
footnotes.body_html: ▼ to my hurt: or, in my hurt

verses.text_plain: If Cain shall be avenged sevenfold, truly Lamech seventy and sevenfold.
verses.verse_html: 24If Cain shall be avenged sevenfold, truly Lamech seventy and sevenfold.

verses.text_plain: And Adam knew his wife again; and she bare a son, and called his name Seth: For God, said she, hath appointed me another seed instead of Abel, whom Cain slew.
verses.verse_html:
25And Adam knew his wife again; and she bare a son, and called his name Seth: For God, said she, hath appointed me another seed instead of Abel, whom Cain slew. ▼
▼ Seth: Heb. Sheth: that is Appointed, or, Put

footnotes.body_text: ▼ Seth: Heb. Sheth: that is Appointed, or, Put
footnotes.body_html: ▼ Seth: Heb. Sheth: that is Appointed, or, Put

verses.text_plain: And to Seth, to him also there was born a son; and he called his name Enos: then began men to call upon the name of the Lord.
verses.verse_html:
26And to Seth, to him also there was born a son; and he called his name Enos: then began men to call upon the name of the Lord. ▼
▼ Enos: Heb. Enosh
 , ▼
▼ to call…: or, to call themselves by the name of the Lord

footnotes.body_text: ▼ to call…: or, to call themselves by the name of the Lord
footnotes.body_html: ▼ to call…: or, to call themselves by the name of the Lord
